# 🧠 Classification Model Analysis

## 🔍 Overview

This project builds a classification model to predict categorical outcomes based on input features.

## 📊 Model Performance

* Accuracy: ~70% – 85%
* Precision & Recall evaluated using confusion matrix
* Balanced performance across classes

## 📈 Key Findings

* Certain features showed strong influence on classification outcome
* Model correctly classified majority of observations
* Some misclassification observed in borderline cases

## 📊 Evaluation Metrics

* Accuracy Score
* Confusion Matrix
* Precision & Recall

## 🔑 Insights

* Model performs well for general prediction
* Sensitive to feature selection and data quality
* Can be improved with advanced models (Random Forest, XGBoost)

## 📌 Conclusion

The classification model provides reliable predictions and demonstrates core supervised learning concepts effectively.
